{"word":"πορεία","slug":"πορεία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πορεία</b></el> <el>(πορεία, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πορεύω'><el>πορεύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a walking, mode of walking</i> or <i>running, gait</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a going, a journey, way, passage</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a march</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a crossing of water, passage</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}